Undid revision 963396368 by [[Special:Contributions/Pickelhaube103|Pickelhaube103]] ([[User talk:Pickelhaube103|talk]]) They were not the only countries included in the Statute of Westminster 1931. Before making any further edits, please be patient and start a discussion on the talk page instead of WP: Edit Warring.

Although they were de jure independent for many years prior, Australia, Canada and New Zealand achieved sovereign status (co-equality with the United Kingdom) with the Statute of Westminster in 1931, granting the regions full legislative independence. This is why the maximum extent of the British empire is measured in 1913, not 1942. As an example, Canada declared war against Nazi Germany on September 10, 1939, a full week later after Britain acted to symbolically demonstrate independence.
Updated description of empire to be more consistent with Japanese page as well as historically defined terms of "Empire" at the time as well as today.
